Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full kettle.

Halve the @green pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips, then cut the strips in half widthways. Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until soft and slightly charred, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Pour the boiled water from your #kettle{} into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @red split lentils{100%g} and bring back to the boil.

Lower the heat and simmer until the lentils are starting to soften, ~{6-7%minutes} - you'll finish cooking them in the soup later. Drain in a #sieve{} and set aside.

In the meantime, peel and grate the @garlic clove{3} (or use a #garlic press{}). Trim the @carrot{1}, then coarsely grate (no need to peel).

Pop the (now empty) saucepan back on high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, add the carrot and stir-fry until slightly tender, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the @cumin seeds{1/2%tsp}, @chermoula spice mix{2%tbsp} and half the garlic, then cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @tomato puree{30%g}, @vegetable stock paste{15%g}, par-cooked lentils, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{550%ml} to the saucepan.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine the remaining garlic with the @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the garlic bread. Season with salt and pepper, then spread over the @plain naans{2}.

Once the pepper is cooked, stir it through the lentil soup. Season with salt and pepper.

Pop the naans onto the (now empty) baking tray and into the oven until starting to turn golden, ~{5-6%minutes}.

When ready, share the soup between your bowls. Drizzle over the @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g} and crumble over the @Greek style salad cheese{100%g}.

Cut the garlic naans into dippers and serve alongside. Enjoy!